Operation.description: Creates persisted or transient VariantRule based on the ConfiguratorContext associated to bomLine and VariantRule applied in BOMWindow. The new VariantRule has bomline specific of features applied to VariantRule on BOMWindow and ConfiguratorContext attached to bomLine. If there is no CC attached to line nothing will be returned.

ServiceData containing new VariantRule. Any failure will be returned with mapped error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors.
    178032: No effective Configurator Context can be found on the BOM Window.
    178002: The received Variant Rule is either null or invalid, when the operation expects a Product Configurator-authored Variant Rule.

Operation.useCase: This operation is meant to be used in a scenario when the user would need to get the SVR of a line or a bomline specific SVR of a child line.

ParameterInfo.description: source BOMLine of an assembly for compare of Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision.

If provided, it will be used for configuration during compare action. Otherwise, the stored RevisionRule of respective Solution Variant ItemRevision is used for configuration during the compare action. Default value is null and this is valid for single Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision.
A list of Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision which needs to be compared.

A map (string/string) of config preferences.
Key: "StopOnError " “True”, “False” :
True: the compare of Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision is stopped when an error is encountered.
False: the compare action continues after an error is encountered at any stage.
If not provided, the default behaviour is false.

Operation.description: This operation compares the input ‘Managed’ category of Solution Variant ItemRevision with the given source BOMLine object. It supports comparison of multiple Solution Variant ItemRevision to common single source BOMLine object. The configured first level structural changes would be compared to respective Solution Variant ItemRevision. Property changes are not considered for comparison report. By default, the stored RevisionRule and VariantRule of respective Solution Variant ItemRevision is used for configuration during the compare action. User can override the RevisionRule for configuration. In case of multiple Solution Variant update, respective Solution Variant RevisionRule will be used.
Operation.name: compareManagedSolutionVariantItems
Operation.returnDescription:
Contains Generic Source ItemRevision and a list of CompareManagedSVItemRevReport structure. Any failure will be returned with mapped error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors.
    178019: Solution Variant ItemRevisions with different category cannot be updated together.
    178020: The source ItemRevision of input Solution variant ItemRevisions and input Generic Variant ItemRevision do not refer to same Generic variant Item.
    178021: Updating RevisionRule for multiple Solution Variant is not supported.
    178022: Invalid input list of Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision is provided.
Operation.useCase:
This operation is suited to compare a Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision with generic assembly.
1. Client opens a generic assembly in Structure Manager.
2. Client will search for solution variant in Solution Variant Search view by using Solution Variant category or using criteria.
3. Client selects Solution Variant ItemRevisions of “Managed” category for update.
4. Client invokes update action for selected Solution Variant ItemRevision objects for updating from a generic BOMLine object.
5. This action first evokes compareManagedSolutionVariantItems operation to get the first level structural differences between the Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and generic assembly ItemRevision.
6. Client uses response from CompareManagedSVItemRevResponse operation to display the first level structural differences between the Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and generic assembly ItemRevision.

Operation.description: This operation creates fully configured Solution Variant assemblies from generic assembly BOMLine objects. This creation is done on input generic assembly BOMLine objects who satisfy the Solution Variant Item creation criteria. Also the newly created Solution Variant Item is replaced on the Solution Variant assembly BOMLine.

Operation.returnDescription:
A list CreateMultilvelSVOutput structure (which contains the generic BOMLine object and ItemRevision object of newly created configured assemblies BOMLine). Also it contains next set of BOMLine objects which will be input for next Solution Variant Item creation with the mapped BOMLine objects UID’s (Unique Identifier) of the Solution Variant assembly. Any failure will be returned with mapped error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors
178018: Invalid preference provided for the Multilevel Solution Variant creation
Operation.useCase:
Use Case:
This operation is suited to create a static snapshot of a configured product structure which represents particular variant from generic assembly after applying variant configuration.
1.Client opens a generic assembly in Structure Manager.
2.Client opens Variant Configuration view.
3.Client selects criteria and apply the configuration criteria on the opened assembly.
4.Client invokes createMultilevelSolutionVariants operation for selected top BOMLine object to create a static snapshot of BOMLine objects configured by the variant configuration only.
5.Client uses response from createMultilevelSolutionVariants operation to decide another iteration required for creation of Solution Variant for next level.

ParameterInfo.description: The source BOMLine of an assembly for the Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision update.

If provided, it will be used for configuration during the update action. Otherwise, the stored RevisionRule of the respective Solution Variant ItemRevision is used for configuration during the update action. This is valid for single Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision.
A list of Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision which needs to be updated.

A map (string,string) of config preferences.
Key: "StopOnError " “True”, “False” :
True: the update of Reuse Solution Variants ItemRevision is stopped when an error is encountered.
False: the update action continues after an error is encountered at any stage.
If not porvided, the default behavior is false.

Operation.description: This operation updates the input Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision from the given source BOMLine object. The configured first level structural changes would be updated in respective Solution Variant ItemRevision. By default, the stored RevisionRule and VariantRule of respective Solution Variant ItemRevision is used for configuration during the update action. User can update the Solution Variant’s RevisionRule by providing the input RevisionRule. In case of multiple Solution Variant update, respective Solution Variant RevisionRule is used.
Operation.name: updateReuseSolutionVariantItems
Operation.returnDescription:
Contains A list UpdateReuseSVItemRevOutput structure (which contains the input Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision and updated Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision). Any failure will be returned with mapped error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors.
    178019: Solution Variant ItemRevisions with different category cannot be updated together.
    178020: The source ItemRevision of input Solution variant ItemRevisions and input Generic Variant ItemRevision do not refer to same Generic variant Item.
    178021: Updating RevisionRule for multiple Solution Variant is not supported.
Operation.useCase:
This operation is suited to update a Reuse Solution Variant ItemRevision from particular generic assembly.
1. Client opens a generic assembly in Structure Manager.
2. Client will search for solution variant in Solution Variant Search view by using Solution Variant category or using criteria.
3. Client selects Solution Variant ItemRevision objects of “Reuse” category for update.
4. Client invokes updateReuseSolutionVariantItems operation for selected Solution Variant ItemRevision objects for updating from a generic BOMLine object.
5. Client uses response from UpdateReuseSVItemRevResponse operation to display updated Solution Variant ItemRevision.

Operation.description:
This operation creates fully configured Solution Variant assemblies from generic assembly BOMLine objects. This creation is done on input generic assembly BOMLine objects who satisfy the Solution Variant Item creation criteria. Also, the newly created Solution Variant Item is replaced on the Solution Variant assembly BOMLine.

The user will receive a notification when this operation completes. The notification message subject has this syntax:
Created new Solution Variant "<object_string of solution variant item>" for generic assembly "<object_string of generic assembly BOMLine object>".

The operation generates a text report consisting of the solution variant creation summary and attaches it to notification object as Dataset. The report has the following syntax:
Solution Variant Creation Report:
==================================================
============= Processing for level 0 started =============
Level 0: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 0 completed ==========

============= Processing for level 1 started =============
Level 1: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
Level 1: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 1 completed ==========

============= Processing for level 2 started =============
Level 2: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 2 completed ==========

Multi-level solution variant create operation completed.

ParameterInfo.description: Source BOMLine of as assembly for Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision update.

If provided, RevisionRule input Solution Variant ItemRevision will be updated. This should be same which was used in CompareManagedSolutionVariantItems operation. Default value is null and this is valid for single Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision update.
A list of CompareManagedSVItemRevReport structure (contains Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and list of CompareReportNode which is to updated in Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision).

A map (string/string) of config preferences.
Key: "StopOnError " “True”, “False” :
True: The update of Managed Solution Variants ItemRevision is stopped when an error encountered.
False: The update action continues after an error is encountered at any stage. If not provided, the default behavior is false.

Operation.description: This operation updates the input ‘Managed’ category of Solution Variant with the input given source BOMLine object. It supports update of multiple Solution Variant ItemRevision to common single source BOMLine object. The response from CompareManagedSolutionVariantItems operation displays the first level structural differences, user selects desired structural changes required in Solution Variant ItemRevision and uses this operation to update the Managed SolutionVariant ItemRevision. User can update the Solution Variant’s RevisionRule by providing the input RevisionRule. This RevisionRule should be same which was used in CompareManagedSolutionVariantItems operation. In case of multiple Solution Variant update, respective RevisionRule of Solution Variant will be used.
Operation.name: updateManagedSolutionVariantItems
Operation.returnDescription:
Contains A list UpdateManagedSVItemRevOutput structure (which contains the input Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and updated Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision). Any failure will be returned with mapped error message in the ServiceData list of partial errors.
    178019: Solution Variant ItemRevisions with different category cannot be updated together.
    178020: The source ItemRevision of input Solution variant ItemRevisions and input Generic Variant ItemRevision do not refer to same Generic Variant Item.
    178021: Updating RevisionRule for multiple Solution Variant is not supported.
Operation.useCase:
This operation is suited to update a Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision from particular generic source BOMLine :
1. Client opens a generic assembly in Structure Manager.
2. Client will search for Solution Variant in Solution Variant Search view by using Solution Variant category or using criteria.
3. Client selects Solution Variant ItemRevisions of “Managed” category for update.
4. Client invokes update action for selected Solution Variant ItemRevision objects for updating from a generic BOMLine object.
5. This action internally first calls compareManagedSolutionVariantItems operation to get the first level structural differences between the Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and generic assembly ItemRevision.
6. User selects the desired structural changes from the comparison dialog between the Generic Variant ItemRevision and Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision and clicks commit action.
8. Client calls updateManagedSolutionVariantItems operation to commit the changes and update the Managed Solution Variant ItemRevision.

OperationTemplate.description:
This operation creates fully configured Solution Variant assemblies from generic assembly BOMLine objects. This creation is done on input generic assembly BOMLine objects who satisfy the Solution Variant Item creation criteria. Also, the newly created Solution Variant Item is replaced on the Solution Variant assembly BOMLine.

The user will receive a notification when this operation completes. The notification message subject has this syntax:
Created new Solution Variant "<object_string of solution variant item>" for generic assembly "<object_string of generic assembly BOMLine object>".

The operation generates a text report consisting of the solution variant creation summary and attaches it to notification object as Dataset. The report has the following syntax:
Solution Variant Creation Report:
==================================================
============= Processing for level 0 started =============
Level 0: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 0 completed ==========

============= Processing for level 1 started =============
Level 1: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
Level 1: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 1 completed ==========

============= Processing for level 2 started =============
Level 2: Created new Solution Variant "<object_string>" for generic assembly "<object_string>".
============= Processing for level 2 completed ==========

Multi-level solution variant create operation completed.

ServiceInterface.description:
Solution variant functionality provides Interfaces to create a fully configured assemblies from generic assemblies. This newly created assembly will have new part number, which represents solution for a particular variant configuration.

This service provides operations related to the Solution Variant Management on PSBOMViewRevision based structure. This service is applicable only for Product Structures that have variability defined in Product Configurator Application.

StructElement.description:
A map (string, int) of search preferences.

Supported key, values and meaning are:

Key: “userOrSystemSelected”
0, 1 : If 1, the search is on the basis of user selected Configuration criteria; otherwise, 0, if the search is on the basis of System or expanded Configuration criteria.

0, 1 : If 1, the search is consider partially matched configuration criteria input values; otherwise, 0, if the search is for the full matched configuration criteria.

Key: “outputPageSize”
Specifies number of Solution Variant Item Revision objects to return in response. When preference is not specified or passed as 0, all objects generated during operation are returned. Other valid value is any positive integer.

StructElement.description:
Map (string, list of strings) of UIDs, these lists are the UIDs of Solution Variant Item revision objects and Relation objects. Key will describe the type of UID’s inserted into it.
For example:
1. Key – ItemRevision, Value – List of UIDs of SV ItemRevision.
2. Key – Smc0SolutionVariantSource, Value – List of UIDs of Smc0SolutionVariantSource relation object.

These objects are not yet loaded in the current service operation.
It will be input for next service operation i.e loadSolutionVariantItems.

StructElement.description: Configution criteria by which assembly is configured.
StructElement.name: configCriteria

StructElement.description:
A map (string/int) of config preferences.
Supported key, values and meanings are:

Key: "StopOnError "
0, 1 : If 1, the creation of Solution Variants should be stopped when error encountered; otherwise, 0, if the creation should be continue after error on any stage.

Key: "DryRun"
0, 1: If 1, then we provide only the information of Auto Solution Variant creation information, but actual creation wont be done.

Key: "NumberOfLinesToProcess"
If the value of this is greater than 0, then those many lines are processed for Solution Variant createion in each iteration. On the basis on this value ExpandedBOMLineMap output will be presented to client.
Else, no pagination is done.
StructElement.name: configPreferences

StructElement.description:
•SOLUTION_VARIANT_CREATION: Created new Solution Variant (SV ItemRevision) for generic (Generic ItemRevision).
•SOLUTION_VARIANT__PLACEHOLDER: (Generic ItemRevision) does not have Solution Variant Category defined, but one of its children has category defined. So (SV ItemRevision) placeholder SV is created.
•SOLUTION_VARIANT_SKIPPED: (Generic ItemRevision) does not have Solution Variant Category defined, no SV created in this iteration.
•SOLUTION_VARIANT_REUSED: Found an existing Solution Variant (SV ItemRevision) to reuse for (Generic ItemRevision).
